{
  "stem": "21626.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "But even while we can, let the stars of the night and the sun of the day be the messengers of our thoughts and our love.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And in that way, we always remained close.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "They couldn't have guessed what a godsend those thoughtful gestures would be, not just to me but to my sister, too.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "Because when war started and all correspondence ceased, we both poured our hearts into our diaries.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And I, as a little girl every night, prayed to God and talked to Mother and Father through the stars.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And if a falling star suddenly appeared, I thought, that must be a special messenger from Mother, you know, and it made all the difference.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "I never felt abandoned by them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "I always felt close to them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember very clearly saying goodbye to Grandfather and Grandmother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And as he praised me and said, you are your mother's child and your father's child, and I know we will always be proud of you, and I felt, I've got to live so that they would be proud of me.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And Grandmother, she went over my face with her hands so carefully as if memorizing every detail.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "It was very hard saying goodbye.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "My mother's sister, Auntie Berta, who was the youngest of the family, lived with them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "She was a spinster, and she was living with them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "She was the skinniest and the most unhealthiest of all the family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And she was very elegant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "And she only tolerated me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "She was very close to my sister because, as I said, she was the serious one and the older one and the dignified one.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
